one-liner explanation for each dependency:

**Spring Web**: Creates REST APIs and web services with embedded server
**Spring Data JPA**: Simplifies database operations with automatic SQL generation
**PostgreSQL Driver**: Connects your app to PostgreSQL database
**Spring Boot DevTools**: Auto-restarts app when code changes for faster development
**Lombok**: Reduces boilerplate code with annotations (getters, setters, constructors)
            ✅ We’re using Lombok for boilerplate code: @Data, @Builder, @NoArgsConstructor, etc.
**Spring Security** (for later): Handles authentication, authorization, and security features


com/ecommerce/
├── controller/       → REST API logic
├── model/            → JPA entities and enums
├── repository/       → Data access layer (Spring Data JPA)
├── service/          → Business logic
├── dto/              → (optional, cleaner API later)
└── EcommerceBackendApplication.java

**model => repository => service => controller**

ecommerce-backend/
├── src/
│   ├── main/
│   │   ├── java/
│   │   │   └── com/ecommerce/
│   │   │       ├── config/
│   │   │       │   └── SecurityConfig.java             # Password encoder bean
│   │   │
│   │   │       ├── controller/
│   │   │       │   └── UserController.java             # /api/users/signup
│   │   │
│   │   │       ├── dto/
│   │   │       │   ├── UserRequestDTO.java             # For user signup request
│   │   │       │   └── UserResponseDTO.java            # For user signup response
│   │   │
│   │   │       ├── exception/
│   │   │       │   └── GlobalExceptionHandler.java     # Handles duplicate email, etc.
│   │   │
│   │   │       ├── model/
│   │   │       │   ├── Role.java                       # Enum: BUYER, SELLER
│   │   │       │   └── User.java                       # JPA Entity for user
│   │   │
│   │   │       ├── repository/
│   │   │       │   └── UserRepository.java             # Extends JpaRepository
│   │   │
│   │   │       ├── service/
│   │   │       │   ├── UserService.java                # Service interface
│   │   │       │   └── UserServiceImpl.java            # Business logic
│   │   │
│   │   │       └── EcommerceBackendApplication.java    # Main Spring Boot app
│   │   │
│   │   └── resources/
│   │       ├── application.yml                         # DB config, JPA settings
│   │       ├── static/
│   │       └── templates/
├── pom.xml